{{Quote|The mark of succession. It's not an actual mark on the body. Only the Council of Ministers can identify it.|[[Veda (Galacian)|Veda]]|<ref name="Jedi Apprentice: The Mark of the Crown">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Mark of the Crown]]''</ref>}}
The '''Mark of the Crown''' was a tradition on [[Gala]] for indicating the rightful heir to the throne. The Mark was very subtle and could only be detected by a specific test.

==Testing for the Mark==
The Mark was known to the [[Council of Ministers]], and they tested the individual in a certain room deep within the palace for the presence of the Mark.
On the blue mosaic floor of the room a silver pattern marked a certain square on the floor. Stepping on the square activated a [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]] system which covered the being in a cascade of lights. If the true heir stood on the tile, they would be outlined by the light, otherwise there would be no shadow.

